      "writtenOn": "2021-06-20T17:33:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi NYA, Your concern is apt. I also don\u0027t like the way I have handled it.\nThe thing is I was not in a good mood while pushing the patchset. Got carried away by the term that Inspect walks the ast through DFS (ignoring the fact that the underlying grammar, and parsing algorithm decides how the parse tree will look like)\n\nHowever, Now it should be okay. Whenever we see an selector expression we won\u0027t dig into the parsetree (makes sense and that also covers something like errors.New and errors.Wrap etc etc). \n\nLet me know what you think.\n\nThanks : )\n-Bisakh",
